# Deployment & Production Workflow

## Deployment Environments
- Development: Local development with hot reload
- Production: Firebase Hosting deployment
- Database: Supabase production instance

## Firebase Deployment
- Project: twisted-hearth-foundation
- Build command: `npm run build`
- Output directory: `dist/`
- Use Firebase CLI for deployment

## Pre-deployment Checklist
1. Ensure all tests pass
2. Build project successfully
3. Check for TypeScript errors
4. Verify environment variables
5. Test database connections
6. Review security settings

## Build Process
- Use Vite for building
- Optimize assets for production
- Minify JavaScript and CSS
- Generate source maps for debugging

## Environment Configuration
- Separate configs for dev/prod
- Use environment variables for API keys
- Configure CORS properly
- Set up proper error logging

## Monitoring
- Monitor application performance
- Track error rates
- Monitor database performance
- Set up alerts for critical issues

## Rollback Strategy
- Keep previous deployments available
- Use Git tags for releases
- Document rollback procedures
- Test rollback process regularly

## Security Considerations
- Use HTTPS in production
- Implement proper authentication
- Validate all inputs
- Use secure headers
- Regular security audits